results.tokenizedHtml: #include <iostream> #include <vector> #include <cmath> #include <algorithm> #include <numeric> /** * Computes the Softmax of a vector of logits. * Formula: sigma(z)_i = exp(z_i) / sum(exp(z_j)) */ std::vector<double> softmax(const std::vector<double>& logits) { if (logits.empty()) return {}; // 1. Find the maximum value for numerical stability double max_logit = *std::max_element(logits.begin(), logits.end()); std::vector<double> probabilities; probabilities.reserve(logits.size()); double sum_exp = 0.0; // 2. Compute exp(x - max) and the sum for (double val : logits) { double e = std::exp(val - max_logit); probabilities.push_back(e); sum_exp += e; } // 3. Normalize the vector for (double& p : probabilities) { p /= sum_exp; } return probabilities; } int main() { // Example logits (e.g., outputs from a final linear layer) std::vector<double> input = {2.0, 1.0, 0.1}; std::vector<double> output = softmax(input); std::cout << "Probabilities:" << std::endl; for (size_t i = 0; i < output.size(); ++i) { std::cout << "Class " << i << ": " << output[i] << std::endl; } return 0; }
